You are working in a Turborepo + pnpm monorepo with Next.js 15 and React 19.

## Project Structure
- apps/client: Main Next.js app
- apps/admin: Admin Next.js app
- apps/storybook: Component library
- packages/ui: Shared UI (shadcn/ui + Radix)
- packages/eslint-config: Shared ESLint config
- packages/tailwind-config: Shared Tailwind config
- packages/typescript-config: Shared TS configs

## Key Rules
- Use `pnpm` as package manager, never npm or yarn
- Internal packages use `@repo/*` scope with `workspace:*` protocol
- Use `@/*` path alias for app-internal imports
- Follow Conventional Commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, refactor:, test:, docs:
- TypeScript strict mode is enforced
- Styling: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui from @repo/ui
- Testing: Vitest (unit), Playwright (E2E)

## When Writing Code
- Shared components belong in packages/ui, not in apps
- Use React Server Components by default in Next.js app router
- Add "use client" directive only when client-side interactivity is needed
- Import UI components: `import { Button } from "@repo/ui/components/button"`
- Import utilities: `import { cn } from "@repo/ui/lib/utils"`
- New features must include unit tests

## Commands
- `pnpm dev` - Start dev servers
- `pnpm build` - Build all
- `pnpm lint` - Lint all
- `pnpm check-types` - Type check
- `pnpm test` - Run unit tests
- `pnpm --filter <app> <script>` - Run per-app script
